Package: GCSFilesystem
Type: Package
Title: Mounting a Google Cloud bucket as local drive
Version: 0.0.99
Date: 2020-08-27
Authors@R: person("Jiefei", "Wang", email = "jwang96@buffalo.edu",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: 
    Mounting a Google Cloud bucket to a local directory. 
    The files in the bucket can be browsed and read as if they are locally stored. 
    For using the package, you need to install GCSDokan on Windows or gcsfuse on Linux and MacOs.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    stats
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    BiocStyle,
    GCSConnection
SystemRequirements:
    GCSDokan for Windows, 
    gcsfuse for Linux and macOs
biocViews: Infrastructure
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
Encoding: UTF-8
VignetteBuilder: knitr
